  "text": "Toll-like receptors (TLRs) play an important role in induction of innate immunity after influenza and other virus infections, but their biological role remains controversial [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Gowen et al., 2006 [CITATION_3] Majde et al., 2010) . On one hand, TLR3-deficient mice were reported to have higher survival [CITATION_4] and milder behavioural changes associated with influenza virus infection (Majde et al., 2010) after challenge with mouse-adapted, low-pathogenic influenza A viruses. Infection of TLR knockout (TLR3 2/2 ) mice with the phlebovirus Punta Toro is associated with reduced disease severity (Gowen et al., 2006) . On the other hand, TLR3",
